  - Cross-section system diagram: GPU die + 3 HBM stacks (each showing 4 DRAM dies + base die with TSVs) on silicon interposer over package substrate
  - Comparison table: HBM2 (7.0), HBM2E (6.5), HBM3 (5.5), HBM3E (5.0) with per-component breakdown
  - Why HBM is most efficient: TSV is 40x less capacitance than PCB (50 fF vs 2 pF), ultra-wide 1024-bit bus enables low per-pin speed (simple NRZ, no PAM),
