  Slide 3 -- GPU SM: The 256 KB SRAM and Its Infrastructure
  - Left: Visual of all 32 SRAM banks (8x4 grid), operand collectors, crossbar, ALUs
  - Right: WHY it must be 256 KB (400-cycle HBM latency -> need 32+ warps -> 128-256 KB minimum)
  - Lists all 6 infrastructure components that exist solely to serve the RF
  - Bottom callout: "The GPU cannot shrink or remove the register file. This is the architecture the TPU and KPU eliminate."

  Slide 4 -- TPU/KPU: Distributed PE-Local Registers
  - Side-by-side diagrams showing PE internals: TPU (W reg + MAC + Accumulator) vs KPU (A/B regs + MAC + C reg + SURE wires)
  - Both have ~128-256 KB total storage but as PE-local latches, not shared SRAM
  - Comparison table: shared SRAM vs distributed latches across 6 dimensions
  - "Can GPU copy this? NO -- would require removing the SIMT model"

  Slide 5 -- Dynamic Energy: Per-Op Operand Delivery (SEPARATE from static)
  - Visual chains showing GPU (9 pipeline stages), TPU (3 stages), KPU (3 stages) with per-stage energies
  - GPU overhead per warp: 6.50 pJ -> per MAC: 0.203 pJ. TPU: ~0.36 pJ/op. KPU: ~0.053 pJ/op
  - GPU-to-KPU overhead ratio: ~4x -- structural advantage GPU cannot replicate

  Slide 6 -- Static Power: The Always-On SRAM Cost (SEPARATE slide)
  - Explains leakage physics: P_static = N_transistors * I_leak * V_dd
  - Per SM: 256 KB -> 50 mW -> 0.26 pJ/MAC (CUDA), 0.13 pJ/MAC (TC)
  - Full GPU: 132 SMs -> 6.6 W RF leakage (0.9% of 700W TDP)
  - TPU/KPU comparison: PE latches leak ~10x less, and KPU can power-gate individual tiles
  - Caveat clearly stated: static is secondary (~0.13-0.26 pJ) vs dynamic RF infrastructure (~0.20 pJ)

  Slide 7 -- Summary Table + Energy Bars
  - Complete table with RF storage type, delivery mechanism, MAC energy, overhead, RF infrastructure cost, static power, total, and efficiency
  - Stacked energy bars: green (MAC) + orange (RF infra) + gray (other overhead) + red (static)
  - Takeaway: GPU TC 1.81 vs KPU 0.96 pJ/op = 1.9x core compute advantage. The 256 KB banked SRAM + delivery infrastructure is the structural cost the GPU
